<item>
            <title>[LU-19081] Unable to build master on ubuntu 24.04 with a newer 6.8.0-60 kernel release.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19081</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are not using hwe-6.11 on this cluster so stuck with 6.8.0 branch on 24.04&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using... ldiskfs-6.8.0-45-ubuntu24.series&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#this breaks on newer releases..&lt;br/&gt;
linux-5.14/ext4-kill-dx-root.patch&lt;br/&gt;
ubuntu20.04.5/ext4-filename-encode.patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#my local hacks...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#this seems to possibly fix first issue. changing to&lt;br/&gt;
linux-6.11/ext4-kill-dx-root.patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#second issue is above my pay grade.. dir.c changes .. backed out this change in the linux source tree&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://git.launchpad.net/~ubuntu-kernel/ubuntu/+source/linux/+git/noble/commit/fs/ext4/dir.c?h=Ubuntu-6.8.0-60.63&amp;amp;id=f227c00de0978038b1b95d1954c2234bb29f51cb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git.launchpad.net/~ubuntu-kernel/ubuntu/+source/linux/+git/noble/commit/fs/ext4/dir.c?h=Ubuntu-6.8.0-60.63&amp;amp;id=f227c00de0978038b1b95d1954c2234bb29f51cb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the two changes above, master builds and seems to work just fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any chance of validating the first change is ok and somehow fix the second issue so master will build normal?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
